review_text:
Swiss Crew is always so professional and friendly. 
for short-haul flights all the basic needs are covered, water, and even a little Swiss-branded chocolate. :-)
When traveling from Switzerland they also offer the Airtrain service that can be very helpful if don't live in Zurich or Geneva.

Swiss International can be a pricy airline but if you catch them at the right time their fares are very reasonable
for the service and really good unboard food selections including their signature brand of Swiss chocolate,
wine and beer are on the house so that alone makes your flight an enjoyble one my airfare was around $840.00 dollars which was not bad when you consider their economy flights to Europe are about $1,300.00 and my price was round trip to China

Delays Happen, flights get cancelled, always a risk when flying... but as far as how we were treated by Swiss air , I can say that I‚Äôm VERY pleased. Compensated with an overnight stay in Zurich at a Hilton hotel and a dinner/ Breakfast included gave us a chance to catch our breath. They rearranged our travel itineraries in a short amount of time while still in palma. I‚Äôve flown a lot of places with various airlines and I am impressed with Swiss air;
 Thank-You!
Gina D
